<br>
- Give me a SPECIFIC example of how a quest is 'BLOCKED'.   Not 'There are some quests', or 'I know this person'.  A proper example would be 'The Xakra Dart Quest cannot be done because of X, Y, Z. which is caused by the TLC.'  Are you simply afraid that people will point out that that quest really is not BLOCKED by the TLC?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   The point is not that there is an exploitive method to get around doing the quest yourself. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
- Explotive?  Using materials purchased from merchants or players is not.  It is actually what was intended for FV.  In fact, the Deves said that you were to use lower level players assistance to help when the TLC barred you from getting an item (see Deve Forum on EQ home page).  So please stop trying to infer some moral inferiority of players that follow the TLC guildlines.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Try a quest sometime without a spoiler page in hand and see how you like the TLC then. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  <br>
<br>
Again, you do not know me.  I have done quest with out the help of spoiler pages (most of the SOL lucin quests are on the spoiler pages).  I do them and (if you read in my above post) I have also had to deal with the TLC.   I still like the TLC.<br>
<br>
Bjord, you may also notice that I have been able to use FACT to disprove everyone of your 'The TLC makes quests impossible' arguments.  <br>
<br>
The TLC works just as it was intended to work.  There is no reason to remove it from the game.  Just because you are incapable to patience or the ability to work with in the rule set of FV does not mean the TLC is broken.<br>
<br>
